Recipe by the one and only @chancy.james ♥️ swipe for some highlights 😅
"How to" video on IGTV!

TAG Your ppl and grab recipe below! 

RECIPE 
Makes two Wellington loaves! Perfect for freezing & baking later too!

Ingredients 
1-2 tbs oil (I used avocado oil)
1 yellow onion (diced)
4 garlic cloves (minced)
8oz of mushrooms (1 container, diced)
2 “ribs” of celery (diced small)
3/4 cup frozen peas
1 (12 oz) package vegan ground “beef” (I used Impossible meat)
1 package of Puff Pastry (includes 2 doughs)
2 tbs cornstarch
2 tbs ground flax w/ 6 tbs water
1/3 tsp salt
1/4 tsp pepper (or grind to liking)
1 tbs dried basil
1 tbs dried thyme 

1. Takeout Puff Pasty dough and vegan ground “beef” to defrost.

2. On medium heat sauté diced onion and garlic for about 2 minutes. Add diced mushroom. Sauté for about 2 more minutes. Add frozen peas and diced celery.

3. Add vegan “beef”, sauté for about 5-7 minutes...You do not need to cook the whole way, anything that is not finished cooking will cook through in the oven.

4. Take mixture off heat and put into a large mixing bowl to cool. Add 2 tbs cornstarch and mix in.

5. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

6. In a small bowl or cup, Mix 2 tbs of ground flax with 6 tbs water. Let sit for 10-15 min while mixture cools. Then add the flax mixture to the "meat" mixture & mix to combine !

7. Once mixture is cool, roll out two puff pastry doughs. Roll gently to evenly spread into large rectangular loaf.

8. Cut slits along side, you will go about 3 inches on each side. Distribute mixture evenly between two puff pastry’s. Fold over slits to create a lattice criss cross design.Tuck in each end to secure mixture.

9. Bake in oven at 400 degrees for 40 minutes or until deep Golden brown. 

10. Let cool for 10 minutes and use bread or serrated knife to slice. Enjoy with Mushroom Gravy or on its own!

POBLANO PEPPER CREMA 
Amazing on just about anything🥲 

Recipe 
2 poblano peppers 
2 jalapeños 
1 cup cashews 
Pinch of salt 
1/2 white onion 
3 garlic cloves 
Handful of cilantro 

1. Soak cashews in hot water for at least 10 minutes. 

2. Roast poblanos peppers & jalapeños until charred over open flame or you can roast them in an air fryer for 6-9 minutes at 400F!

3.  Put the peppers in a bowl and cover with plastic and let sit for 5 minutes. 

4. In a pan char onion (roughly chopped) and garlic. 

5. Peel and remove seeds from peppers then place in blender with onion, garlic, cilantro, good pinch salt and (drained) cashews. Add 1/2 cup oh hot water and blend on high until smooth. Add more water if needed!

6. Store in a jar sealed in fridge for up to 6 days. Use on sandwiches, burgers, & of course tacos!

FROZEN MEXICAN HOT CHOCOLATE 
Chocolate, cinnamon & vanilla slushy! SO BEYOND DELISH

I am in love with all that Mexican hot chocolate has to offer, but with this summer heat this is the solution 😙

It’s perfectly sweet, satisfying and delish and refreshing. 
#Osterpartner I have teamed up with @osterkitchen ! 

Using @osterkitchen One Touch Blender available at Walmart! #Blendlesspossiblities

RECIPE

2 ounces dark chocolate, chopped 
1 tbsp cocoa powder 
2 cups oat milk (or any non dairy milk) 
1 cinnamon stick (or 1/4 tsp ground cinnamon)
1 tsp vanilla extract 
2 tbsp pure maple syrup 
Small pinch of salt 
Couple handfuls of ice 

In a pot combine 1 cup of non dairy milk,dark chocolate, cinnamon, vanilla, cocoa powder & pure maple syrup …mix over medium / low heat and let the chocolate fully melt. Remove cinnamon stick 

In a @osterkitchen One-Touch Blender add a cup of non dairy milk, the chocolate mixture, and a couple handfuls of ice. Blend in high until slushy consistency is reached. Enjoy!

ROASTED GARLIC HERB BUTTER 🧈 
Who else has a love for butter in a flour tortilla 🤍 

RECIPE 
1 head of garlic 
1 tbsp olive oil 
1 stick of vegan butter (I used earth balance)
1 tsp dried oregano 
1 tsp dried thyme 
1 tsp dried basil 

Take vegan butter out from the fridge to let it softened / come to room temp.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. 

Cut a bit off the top of a whole garlic head. Then add to a piece of foil and drizzle with olive oil. Wrap it up and bake it oven for 45 minutes or until golden surface forms. 

To a bowl add softened butter, squeeze roasted garlic in, add dried herbs, mix well and enjoy straight away or wrap in plastic wrap whatever way you want and pop in freezed for 35 mins or fridge for an hour to harden up. 

Use in pasta, on bread,
Flour tortillas and Store remaining in fridge!

AGUA DE SANDIA 
Watermelon water😗 TAG your ppl and make ASAP! 

RECIPE
•Watermelon (I used a mini watermelon) 

•1/4 cup -1 cup sugar (depending on your sweetness preference and how sweet your 🍉 is) 

•Couple limes (kinda optional but If you want it to last in your fridge for 3 days add the Lime juice! )

1. Add cut watermelon to blender. Blend on high for 1 min or until smooth. Use a mesh strainer to strain into pitcher or you can keep pulp too!

2. Add 2-3 cups water and sugar to taste! You can add lime juice if you wish for citrus flavor and if you want to store some in fridge for 2-3 days definitely add lime to help preserve it!

3. Serve with lots of ice!

CHEESY STUFFED FLOR DE CALABAZA (squash blossom) TACOS🤍 

SAVE & tag your ppl and please make these bbs 🥲 they’re so good 😭

RECIPE

Corn tortillas 
Your favorite vegan cheese (I used fresh moz by @miyokoscreamery) 
Squash blossoms (flor the calabaza) 
Avocado 
Salsa 
Cilantro 

Bring a pan to medium heat

Cut the bottom of the squash blossom and remove the little bud. Then stuff with a piece of cheese. 

Add 1-2 tbsp  of oil to your pan and add the Vegan cheese stuffed squash blossoms. Pan fry on both sides for 30 seconds or so or until cheese is melty and the flowers get some color. 

Heat your tortillas, add the cheese stuffed blossoms, add avocado, salsa, cilantro and ENJOYYYY🤍

CAFÉ DE OLLA 🇲🇽
Tag your ppl below, save this post and make this weekend, you won’t regret it 🥲🤍 

Collaboration with @lifemeasuredbytaylor digital kitchen scale to precisely weigh ingredients☕️ #ad #livemeasured #taylorUSA

RECIPE
8 cups water 
40 grams (1/2 cup) ground coffee 
1 piloncillo (or half if you want it less sweet) [OR you can use brown sugar (about heaping tbsp sugar per cup of water]
4 cloves 
1 cinnamon stick 

Measure 40 grams of coffee (I used @lifemeasuredbytaylor digital kitchen scale)

Add 8 cups Filtered  water to your pot. *you can use any pot if you don’t have a Mexican barro pot*. 

Then add in piloncillo, cinnamon stick and cloves. Being to a soft boil for 25 minutes then add in coffee, stir in. Then turn off heat. Let the coffee steep for 15-20 minutes. 
using a fine mesh strainer, strain the coffee then serve To your liking!

HIBISCUS SALT 🌺 
Tag your ppl, save and use this beautiful salt for your cocktails & or as a topping !

RECIPE:

•6 ounces (about 1/2 + 2 tbsp) Coarse kosher salt (or you can use margarita salt)
•2 (packed) cups dried hibiscus flowers 
•1/3 cup cane sugar 

Add dried flowers to food processor and process for 1 min then add in sugar and salt. Pulse really for 2-3 minutes until it comes together! 

May come together faster if your flowers are smaller.

HOMEMADE TORTILLAS made with my whole 🤍 + some pressed squash blossoms

SAVE & tag your ppl below! 

so easy & delish!

RECIPE 
Makes 8 tortillas 

1 cup instant corn masa flour ( I use the brand Maseca, either white or yellow…both are great) 
3/4 cup + 1 tbsp (room temp) water 
Pinch of salt 
(Optional) squash blossoms

In a bowl, add the corn masa flour. Add a good pinch of salt then add most the water, leaving about 1/4 out. Mix with your hands then add in the remaining water and really bring the masa together using your hands. Will be slightly sticky….shouldn’t be dry! If so add a splash more of water. 

Cover with plastic wrap and let it rest for 15-20 minutes.

Meanwhile if you’re using squash blossoms, cut off the bottom and remove the inside bulb. 

Prep your tortilla press with plastic. I think a large zip lock cut is the best but if not parchment paper can work too. 

Bring hot pan or comal to medium / high heat. 

Begin to roll your tortillas into golf size balls. Place masa ball to the bottom of tortilla press on one of the pieces of plastic. Then cover with the other plastic and gently press to flatten a bit, then open it up,
Remove plastic then add the squash blossom to center, add plastic back on top then press down using the tortilla press handle. 

If you’re not adding squash blossom then just press down with handle right away. 

Add tortilla to your hot pan and cook for about less then 1 min on head side, look for the air bubbles to form! 

Enjoy!!!

VEGAN CHEESE STUFFED JALAPEÑO CARNE ASADA TACOS 
Tag ur ppl & save🤍
“How to” / more info on ig stories! 

Inspo from @freddsters !

RECIPE
Makes 8 tacos 
Ingredients: 
8 jalapeños 
8 ounces vegan cheese 

Vegan “carne asada”
1 (heaping) cup Texture soy (TVP: textured vegetable protein)

2 tsp bouillon paste (I recommend the vegetarian chicken or beef )
1/4 cup soy sauce 
1 tbsp brown sugar 
1/2 tsp ground cumin 
Juice of 1 lime 
3 tbsp salsa (optional) 

1/4 onion diced small 
3 cloves garlic, minced 
Good Pinch of salt and pepper 

Small handful cilantro, chopped 
1/4 onion, diced small 
Corn or flour tortillas 
2-3 limes 
Salsa for serving 

Easy guacamole:
2 ripe avocados 
Juice of 1 lime
Pinch of salt and pepper
1 tsp garlic powder 
1 tsp onion powder 

1. To a large bowl add a heaping cup of textured soy. Cover completely with hot water. Then add in 2 tsp bouillon paste.

2. Let it soak for 12 minutes 

3. Meanwhile roast your jalapeños in oven at 450 F for 9-12 minutes (flipping half way through) or on stove top until charred on both sides. Add peppers to a bowl and cover with plastic wrap & let sit for 6 minutes. 

4. Back to the textured soy, strain and then leave in the same bowl. To a separate bowl add soy sauce or Tamari, juice of a lime, 1 tbsp brown sugar and 1/2 tsp ground cumin.  Mix. Then add to the texture soy. Combine well. 

5. Heat a large pan over medium heat. Add 3-4 tbsp oil, then once hot add in the texture soy with all the marinade (CAREFUL) when you add it in! Juices may jump!

6. Let it cook until all the juices have evaporated. 

7. It will evaporate after 5 ish minutes. Season well with salt & pepper. Then add in 1/4 (finely diced) onion and 3 cloves (minced) garlic. Mix to combine. Cook for a few more minutes. Allow for it to get charred and deeper in color. You can add an a optional few spoonfuls of salsa and mix again.

8. Return to jalapeños. Peel & create a slit to remove seeds. Stuff with vegan cheese. Melt them in an airfryer at 400 for 6 minutes or in the microwave for less then a min.

9. Form your tacos. Heat up tortilla, add cheese stuffed jalapeño, soy carne asada, salsa, finely diced onion and cilantro and guacamole!

FRIJOLES DE LA OLLA
A pot of beans made with lots of love. If you grew up in Mexican / Latin household you knew when a delicious pot of beans were cooking up.

I used @Cookwithbeautiful Dutch oven by @Drewbarrymore available at @Walmart! #MakeSomethingBeautiful
The quality of Beautiful Dutch oven is incredible and so perfect for this recipe that is made weekly in our home!
3 cups of pinto beans 
3/4 of a white onion
6 cloves garlic
salt
Filtered water
Other ingredients : 
Avocado
Cilantro
1/4 onion, diced very small 
Tortilla
(optional) shredded (vegan) cheese (optional) Fresh jalapeño, diced very small
Method:
Sort through your beans and remove any pebbles or small rocks. You may find 1-2 in each batch of beans. Strain your beans really well then add to @Cookwithbeautiful Dutch oven. Cover the beans with filtered water, you want about 1-2 inches of water above the beans. Add in onion (cut in big chunks) and peeled whole garlic cloves. DO NOT ADD SALT AT THIS POINT...WE WILL ADD LATER!
With the lid off, cook the beans for around 2 hours or more or until the beans are fully cooked, soft and tender. Throughout the cooking process you will need to add 2-3 cups of additional (HOT) filtered water as the water in the pot will begin to evaporate and you want more of a soup consistency.
Once the beans are cooked and tender add a generous 2 pinches of salt, mix then taste, add more salt to your liking.
Before serving you can remove the garlic and onion but I personally like to leave them in! Serve beans hot with bean broth, top off with chopped cilantro, onion, avocado and a side of tortilla.
